    Class and Description
    ConditionalTwoCoinChannel
    Informants may use two-coin channels (see TwoCoinChannel) to communicate information about a Boolean-valued secret to spies.

    A spy's knowledge of a Boolean-valued secret is described by a distribution describing the likelihood that the secret is true and the likelihood that the secret is false.
